						<summary>

						<p>On a stone in a field to the south of the village.</p>						

						<p>The record is dated Śaka 1434, <hi rend="italic">Āngi[rasa]</hi> • • • • • 15. The date could be after A.D. 1512, March 18.</p>						

						<p>Fragmentary. Seems to register a land grant in Kasavānūru by Yallama-nāyaka of Iḍumula<hi rend="italic">gōtra</hi> to Parvatayya, Rāmayya, Jannayya and Gannayya of Ṛik-<hi rend="italic">śākhā</hi> and Vishṇuvardhana-<hi rend="italic">gōtra.</hi> Other details of the record are lost.</p>						

						</summary>
